text: Black Oak is an unincorporated community in Caldwell County, in the U.S. state of Missouri. ==History== Black Oak was platted in the early 1870s, and named for a grove of black oak trees near the original town site. A post office called Black Oak was established in 1868, and remained in operation until 1904. ==References== Category:Unincorporated communities in Caldwell County, Missouri Category:1868 establishments in Missouri Category:Unincorporated communities in Missouri
title: Black Oak, Missouri
